<br>
Taunt doesn't work on 63+ level mobs.  So there goes the warrior's claim to fame.  All they stand on is Def disc and hit points.<br>
<br>
<br>
With upper level gear Monks have the HPs to tank and our defensive skills dwarf a warriors like the sun compared to the moon.<br>
<br>
<br>
Def disc stands against you in a raid situation in 2 ways.  #1 you use it as a crutch because you know no better because you are doing it &quot;like everyone else has&quot; and def disc has a refresh rate which forces you to rotate warriors for their disc which leaves a hole if you only have 1 or 2 flagship MT warriors with the gear needed.  #2 It decreases the warriors damage output which makes all the support melee have to back off their damage which makes the fight last longer and wastes mana just the same as the extra clerics it takes to keep the same monk MT alive.<br>
